   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Ancient Greek Text Analysis with XNAi Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the integration of JupyterLab with XNAi Foundation's research environment for analyzing ancient Greek texts.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Features demonstrated:**\n",
    "- Ancient Greek text processing with CLTK\n",
    "- Integration with Vikunja task management\n",
    "- Local model routing for translation and analysis\n",
    "- Research task tracking and progress monitoring"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import required libraries\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('/home/jovyan/work/scripts')\n",
    "\n",
    "# XNAi Foundation integration\n",
    "from jupyter_vikunja_integration import (\n",
    "    init_research_environment,\n",
    "    create_task_from_notebook,\n",
    "    get_tasks_from_notebook\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Classical text processing\n",
    "import cltk\n",
    "from cltk.corpus.greek.alphabet import normalize_grc\n",
    "from cltk.tokenize.word import WordTokenizer\n",
    "from cltk.tokenize.sentence import SentenceTokenizer\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data analysis\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configure plotting\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"husl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ All libraries imported successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Initialize Research Environment"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize the research environment\n",
    "env = init_research_environment()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a research task for this analysis\n",
    "research_task = create_task_from_notebook(\n",
    "    title=\"Ancient Greek Text Analysis\",\n",
    "    description=\"Analyze the provided ancient Greek text for linguistic patterns, word frequency, and semantic content.\",\n",
    "    project=\"Classical Studies\",\n",
    "    job_type=\"analysis\",\n",
    "    content=\"\"\"\n",
    "    Ἐν ἀρχῇ ἦν ὁ λόγος, καὶ ὁ λόγος ἦν πρὸς τὸν θεόν, καὶ θεὸς ἦν ὁ λόγος.\n",
    "    οὗτος ἦν ἐν ἀρχῇ πρὸς τὸν θεόν.\n",
    "    πάντα δι' αὐτοῦ ἐγένετο, καὶ χωρὶς αὐτοῦ ἐγένετο οὐδὲ ἕν ὃ γέγονεν.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "if research_task:\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Research task created: {research_task['id']}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Title: {research_task['title']}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Project: {research_task['project_id']}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"❌ Failed to create research task\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Load and Process Ancient Greek Text"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Sample ancient Greek text (John 1:1-3)\n",
    "greek_text = \"\"\"\n",
    "Ἐν ἀρχῇ ἦν ὁ λόγος, καὶ ὁ λόγος ἦν πρὸς τὸν θεόν, καὶ θεὸς ἦν ὁ λόγος.\n",
    "οὗτος ἦν ἐν ἀρχῇ πρὸς τὸν θεόν.\n",
    "πάντα δι' αὐτοῦ ἐγένετο, καὶ χωρὶς αὐτοῦ ἐγένετο οὐδὲ ἕν ὃ γέγονεν.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Normalize the text\n",
    "normalized_text = normalize_grc(greek_text)\n",
    "print(\"Original text:\")\n",
    "print(greek_text)\n",
    "print(\"\\nNormalized text:\")\n",
    "print(normalized_text)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Tokenize and Analyze Text"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize tokenizers\n",
    "word_tokenizer = WordTokenizer('greek')\n",
    "sentence_tokenizer = SentenceTokenizer('greek')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tokenize text\n",
    "words = word_tokenizer.tokenize(normalized_text)\n",
    "sentences = sentence_tokenizer.tokenize(normalized_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total words: {len(words)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total sentences: {len(sentences)}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 10 words:\")\n",
    "print(words[:10])\n",
    "print(\"\\nSentences:\")\n",
    "for i, sentence in enumerate(sentences, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}. {sentence}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Word Frequency Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter out punctuation and create frequency analysis\n",
    "import re\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clean words (remove punctuation)\n",
    "clean_words = []\n",
    "for word in words:\n",
    "    # Remove punctuation\n",
    "    clean_word = re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', word)\n",
    "    if clean_word and len(clean_word) > 1:  # Filter out single characters\n",
    "        clean_words.append(clean_word.lower())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Count frequencies\n",
    "word_freq = Counter(clean_words)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create DataFrame for analysis\n",
    "freq_df = pd.DataFrame(word_freq.items(), columns=['Word', 'Frequency'])\n",
    "freq_df = freq_df.sort_values('Frequency', ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Word Frequency Analysis:\")\n",
    "print(freq_df.head(10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Update task progress\n",
    "if research_task:\n",
    "    env.update_task_progress(research_task['id'], 40, \"Completed word frequency analysis\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Visualize Results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create visualizations\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Top 10 most frequent words\n",
    "top_words = freq_df.head(10)\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=top_words, x='Frequency', y='Word', ax=ax1, palette='viridis')\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Top 10 Most Frequent Words')\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel('Frequency')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Word length distribution\n",
    "word_lengths = [len(word) for word in clean_words]\n",
    "sns.histplot(word_lengths, bins=10, kde=True, ax=ax2, color='skyblue')\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Word Length Distribution')\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel('Word Length')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Update task progress\n",
    "if research_task:\n",
    "    env.update_task_progress(research_task['id'], 70, \"Completed visualization and analysis\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6: Semantic Analysis and Translation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create translation task\n",
    "translation_task = create_task_from_notebook(\n",
    "    title=\"Translate Ancient Greek Text\",\n",
    "    description=\"Translate the analyzed Greek text to English using appropriate models.\",\n",
    "    project=\"Classical Studies\",\n",
    "    job_type=\"translation\",\n",
    "    content=greek_text\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "if translation_task:\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Translation task created: {translation_task['id']}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Model selected: {translation_task.get('metadata', {}).get('routing_info', {}).get('model', 'Unknown')}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Analyze key theological terms\n",
    "theological_terms = ['λόγος', 'θεός', 'ἀρχῇ', 'πάντα']\n",
    "term_analysis = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for term in theological_terms:\n",
    "    frequency = word_freq.get(term.lower(), 0)\n",
    "    term_analysis[term] = {\n",
    "        'frequency': frequency,\n",
    "        'percentage': (frequency / len(clean_words)) * 100 if len(clean_words) > 0 else 0\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nTheological Term Analysis:\")\n",
    "for term, data in term_analysis.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"{term}: {data['frequency']} occurrences ({data['percentage']:.1f}%)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 7: Research Summary and Task Completion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Generate research summary\n",
    "summary = f\"\"\"\n",
    "## Research Summary: Ancient Greek Text Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "### Text Analyzed\n",
    "- Source: John 1:1-3 (Koine Greek)\n",
    "- Total words: {len(clean_words)}\n",
    "- Total sentences: {len(sentences)}\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Findings\n",
    "- Most frequent word: {freq_df.iloc[0]['Word']} ({freq_df.iloc[0]['Frequency']} occurrences)\n",
    "- Average word length: {sum(word_lengths) / len(word_lengths):.1f} characters\n",
    "- Theological terms identified: {len(theological_terms)}\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theological Analysis\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "for term, data in term_analysis.items():\n",
    "    summary += f\"- {term}: {data['frequency']} occurrences ({data['percentage']:.1f}% of text)\\n\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(summary)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Complete the research task\n",
    "if research_task:\n",
    "    completion_notes = f\"\"\"\n",
    "Research completed successfully!\n",
    "\n",
    "Analysis Summary:\n",
    "- Processed {len(clean_words)} words\n",
    "- Identified {len(theological_terms)} key theological terms\n",
    "- Created visualizations for word frequency and length distribution\n",
    "- Generated translation task for further analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Next steps:\n",
    "- Review translation results\n",
    "- Conduct deeper semantic analysis\n",
    "- Compare with other biblical texts\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    success = env.complete_research_task(research_task['id'], completion_notes)\n",
    "    if success:\n",
    "        print(\"✅ Research task completed successfully!\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"❌ Failed to complete research task\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n🎉 Ancient Greek text analysis complete!\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
